Part A: Query Side — "knee arthroplasty"

The query goes through the exact same Stages 1–8 as a document. This ensures query topic centroids and document topic centroids are built by identical logic — Pass 1 is a true like-for-like comparison.

A1. Stage 1: CUI Extraction + ConText

Parameter = Value	Why This Value
TOP_K = 6	Raised from 3. Short phrases like 'pain' or 'fever' often have the correct CUI ranked 4th–5th in embedding search. top_k=3 missed them. 6 gives a safety margin without flooding with noise.
TOP_P = 5000	Candidate pool before ranking. The API searches 2.3M UMLS CUIs but only ranks the closest 5000 by embedding similarity. Larger pools give diminishing returns (the 5001st candidate is never relevant) but cost more compute.
COMBINED = True	Phrase + context sentence are concatenated before embedding lookup. Without context, 'cold' could mean temperature or common cold. The surrounding sentence disambiguates. Tested: True gives 15–20% better precision.
CLUSTER_SET = umls	Search over the full UMLS embedding index (all vocabularies). Narrower cluster sets miss cross-vocabulary matches. SAB filtering in Stage 2 handles vocabulary selection after extraction.
_API_TIMEOUT = 200s	The extraction API can take 30–60s for large batches. 200s gives 3× headroom. Lower timeouts caused false failures during peak load.
_RETRY = 3/1s on 429,5xx	Standard exponential backoff. 3 retries with 1s base covers transient API failures (rate limits, cold starts). 401 triggers token refresh instead of retry.
_GCLOUD_TIMEOUT = 30s	Token fetch via gcloud CLI. Usually <2s, but on cold start or network congestion can take 10–15s. 30s is safe ceiling.
ConText = 102 built-in rules	medspacy’s published rules (Chapman 2001, Harkema 2009). Validated on clinical corpora. Zero custom rules in application code — maintenance is the package team’s responsibility, not ours.

