Why Louvain is skipped for this document: No single entity has more than 22 CUIs after hierarchy reduction. The Louvain threshold is 20. Since the pipeline runs per entity, not on the combined 209 CUIs, every entity takes the fast path.

When WOULD Louvain run? If you had a very long clinical phrase that extracted >20 SNOMED CUIs after hierarchy reduction. For example, a complex surgical procedure description might produce 30+ SNOMED concepts. In that case, Louvain would build a cosine k-NN graph, detect communities, apply silhouette-based splitting, and then run Otsu + guards within each community.

Worked Example: "severe persistent asthma" (19 → 13)

Input: 19 SNOMED CUIs after hierarchy reduction. All have embeddings.

Step 1 — Otsu threshold: Cosine distance matrix: 19×19 = 171 pairwise distances. Otsu splits them into "close" and "far" clusters. Finds tight_t. Capped at median distance.

Step 2 — HAC clustering: Hierarchical Agglomerative Clustering (average linkage) at distance = tight_t groups the 19 CUIs into sub-clusters of very similar concepts.

Step 3 — Per-cluster dedup: Within each sub-cluster, pairs are checked against 4 structural guards (same as query side):
  Guard 1: Direct hierarchy edge? (O(1))
  Guard 2: Semantic types disjoint? (O(|types|))
  Guard 3: Disjoint ancestor sets? (BFS UP [1,5] hops)
  Guard 4: Sibling leaf nodes? (O(1))

